<ns1765:section xmlns:ns1765="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xml:id="resources.information.tecnologies.java.j2se.java2D.java2DImageProcessing.colorInversion">

    <ns1766:title xmlns:ns1766="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Color Inversion (Negative Images)</ns1766:title>

<ns1767:para xmlns:ns1767="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Color inversion is achieved by simply inverting the picel intensities, <ns1768:abbrev xmlns:ns1768="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">i.e.</ns1768:abbrev>
if the original pixel intensity was $i$, the transformed pixel intensity is
$255 - i$.</ns1767:para>
    
